olive oil
½ bunch baby broccoli
1 packet chicken thigh
20 g butter
1 packet garlic paste
1 packet jasmine rice
1.5 cup water
1 sachet Brown Mustard Seeds
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
1 packet Mild Curry Paste
½ packet cream
1 packet parsley
1 packet Onion Chutney
1 packet Greek-Style Yoghurt

• Cut baby broccoli into thirds.
• Cut chicken thigh into 2cm chunks.

• In a medium saucepan, heat the butter with a dash of olive oil over medium heat. Cook half the garlic paste until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Add jasmine rice, the water and a generous pinch of salt, stir, then bring to the boil. Reduce heat to low and cover with a lid.
• Cook for 12 minutes, then remove from heat and keep covered until rice is tender and water is absorbed, 10-15 minutes.

TIP: Cover the pan with a lid if the garlic paste starts to spatter!

• When the rice has 10 minutes remaining, heat a large frying pan over high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook chicken and baby broccoli, tossing occasionally, until chicken is browned and cooked through, 5-6 minutes.
• Add brown mustard seeds, Mumbai spice blend and remaining garlic paste, cooking until fragrant, 1-2 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium, then add mild curry paste, cream (see
ingredients) and a splash of water. Stir to combine and simmer until slightly reduced, 1-2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.

• Divide garlic rice between bowls. Top with chicken and baby broccoli korma.
• Tear over parsley. Serve with a dollop of onion chutney and Greek-style yoghurt. Enjoy!